{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id78a53342-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s823"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"823"},"text":"§ 823.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Repeal of inconsistent laws","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All Acts or parts of Acts inconsistent with this chapter are repealed: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That nothing contained herein shall be held or construed to modify or repeal any of the provisions of the Act of Congress approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 1913","children":[],"tail":", granting certain rights-of-way to the city and county of San Francisco, in the State of California."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id78a53343-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-10/ch285"},"text":"June 10, 1920, ch. 285","children":[],"tail":", pt. I, § 29, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/1077"},"text":"41 Stat. 1077","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered pt. I, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-26/ch687"},"text":"Aug. 26, 1935, ch. 687","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 212, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/847"},"text":"49 Stat. 847","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id78a53344-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id78a53345-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id78a53346-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Herein, referred to in text, means act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1920","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Act of Congress approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 1913","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, was not classified to the Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id78a53347-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As originally enacted, this section contained the further proviso: ","children":[{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{},"text":"“That section 18 of an Act making appropriations for the construction, repair and preservation, of certain public works on rivers and harbors, and for other purposes, approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1917-08-08"},"text":"August 8, 1917","children":[],"tail":", is hereby repealed.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
